subway <- readr::read_csv('data/nta-subway-times.csv')
## Rows: 1225 Columns: 5
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (3): trip, nta_one, nta_two
## dbl (2): S000, seconds_in_transit
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
subway_frame <- dplyr::data_frame(from = subway$nta_one, to = subway$nta_two, weight = 1 / subway$seconds_in_transit)
## Warning: `data_frame()` was deprecated in tibble 1.1.0.
##  Please use `tibble()` instead.
subway_graph <- igraph::graph.data.frame(subway_frame)
subway_matrix <- igraph::as_adjacency_matrix(subway_graph, attr = "weight")
subway_weights <- subway_matrix %>%
  spdep::mat2listw()
## Warning in sn2listw(df): BK96 is not an origin
bk_name <- "Brooklyn"
bk_county_code <- "047"
bk_parks <- "BK99"

bk_nta_borders <- sf::st_read('./data/nyc_2010_nta_borders.geojson') %>%
  dplyr::filter(BoroName == bk_name)  %>%
  dplyr::filter(NTACode != bk_parks) %>%
  dplyr::select("NTACode", "Shape__Area", "Shape__Length", "geometry")
## Reading layer `nyc_2010_nta_borders' from data source 
##   `/home/miller/GeoI/fall-2022/gtech_705-spatial_anlysis/triboro-line/brooklyn-lodes/data/nyc_2010_nta_borders.geojson' 
##   using driver `GeoJSON'
## Simple feature collection with 195 features and 8 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -74.25559 ymin: 40.49614 xmax: -73.70001 ymax: 40.91554
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
bk_od_tract <- readr::read_csv("./data/ny_od_main_JT00_2019.csv") %>%
  dplyr::filter(
      stringr::str_sub(as.character(w_geocode), 3, 5) == bk_county_code &
      stringr::str_sub(as.character(h_geocode), 3, 5) == bk_county_code
  ) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
   w_tract = stringr::str_sub(as.character(w_geocode), 6, 11)
  ) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
   h_tract = stringr::str_sub(as.character(h_geocode), 6, 11)
  ) %>%
  dplyr::select("w_tract", "h_tract", "S000")
bk_tract_nta_equiv <- readxl::read_xlsx('./data/nyc_2010_census_tract_nta_equiv.xlsx') %>%
  dplyr::filter(borough_name == bk_name) %>%
  dplyr::filter(nta_code != bk_parks) %>%
  dplyr::rename(tract = census_tract) %>%
  dplyr::select("tract", "nta_code")

bk_od <- bk_od_tract %>%
  dplyr::left_join(bk_tract_nta_equiv, c("w_tract" = "tract")) %>%
  dplyr::rename(w_nta_code = nta_code) %>%
  dplyr::left_join(bk_tract_nta_equiv, c("h_tract" = "tract")) %>%
  dplyr::rename(h_nta_code = nta_code) %>%
  dplyr::select("h_nta_code", "w_nta_code", "S000") %>%
  dplyr::filter(w_nta_code != bk_parks & h_nta_code != bk_parks)
bk_dest <- bk_od %>%
  dplyr::group_by(w_nta_code) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(
    S000 = sum(S000)
  ) %>%
  unique()

bk_dest_borders <- bk_dest %>%
  dplyr::left_join(bk_nta_borders, c("w_nta_code" = "NTACode")) %>%
  sf::st_as_sf()
subway_global_morans <- spdep::moran.test(bk_dest_borders$S000, subway_weights, zero.policy = TRUE)
subway_global_morans
## 
##  Moran I test under randomisation
## 
## data:  bk_dest_borders$S000  
## weights: subway_weights  n reduced by no-neighbour observations
##   
## 
## Moran I statistic standard deviate = 0.094273, p-value = 0.4624
## alternative hypothesis: greater
## sample estimates:
## Moran I statistic       Expectation          Variance 
##     -0.0198341020     -0.0208333333      0.0001123452
subway_bk_lisa <- spdep::localmoran(
  bk_dest_borders$S000,
  subway_weights,
  zero.policy = TRUE,
  na.action = na.omit,
)

sig_lev <- 0.05
avg_jobs <- mean(bk_dest$S000)

bk_lisa_classes <- subway_bk_lisa %>%
  tibble::as_tibble() %>%
  magrittr::set_colnames(
    c("Ii","E.Ii","Var.Ii","Z.Ii","Pr(z > 0)")
  ) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
    coType = dplyr::case_when(
      `Pr(z > 0)` > 0.05 ~ "Insignificant",
      `Pr(z > 0)` <= 0.05 & Ii >= 0 & bk_dest_borders$S000 >= avg_jobs ~ "HH",
      `Pr(z > 0)` <= 0.05 & Ii >= 0 & bk_dest_borders$S000 <  avg_jobs ~ "LL",
      `Pr(z > 0)` <= 0.05 & Ii < 0 & bk_dest_borders$S000 >= avg_jobs ~ "HL",
      `Pr(z > 0)` <= 0.05 & Ii < 0 & bk_dest_borders$S000 < avg_jobs ~ "LH"
    )
  )

bk_dest_borders$coType <- bk_lisa_classes$coType %>% tidyr::replace_na("Insignificant")

ggplot(bk_dest_borders) +
  geom_sf(aes(
    fill=coType
  ),
  color = 'lightgrey'
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c("red", "NA","blue"),
    name = "Clusters & \nOutliers"
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Job count at nta level"
  )

t_subway_frame <- dplyr::data_frame(from = subway$nta_one, to = subway$nta_two, weight = (1 / (subway$seconds_in_transit ^ (1/8))))

t_subway_graph <- igraph::graph.data.frame(t_subway_frame)

  spdep::mat2listw()

  zero.policy = TRUE,
)
print(t_subway_global_morans)

summary(lines$line_count)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   0.000   1.000   2.000   1.661   2.000   4.000
subway_connected <- subway %>%
  dplyr::left_join(lines) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
    connected_seconds = ifelse(line_count > 0, seconds_in_transit, Inf),
    i_connected_seconds = 1 / connected_seconds^(1 / 8),
    log_S000 = S000
    )
## Joining, by = c("trip", "S000", "nta_one", "nta_two")

  to = subway_connected$nta_two,
  weight = subway_connected$i_connected_seconds,
)
